# Git: no automatic commits or pushes

- **Do not** run `git commit`, `git add` for committing, or `git push` unless the user **explicitly** asks (e.g. "commit", "דחוף", "push to GitHub").
- It is fine to run read-only git commands (`git status`, `git log`, `git diff`) when needed to investigate.
- After code changes, leave the working tree as-is or summarize what changed; the user will commit manually when they want.
